# Shell scripts must stay LF on every platform. A bash script checked out with
# CRLF gets a `\r` appended to its shebang and to every string value (paths,
# command names), which breaks it on macOS/Linux AND in Windows Git-Bash.
# This matters most for the plugin's bin/ launchers and SessionStart hooks,
# which run as real shell processes.
*.sh    text eol=lf
bx/bin/* text eol=lf
